            <tr>
                <td width="14%">1. Goals</td>
                <td width="86%" colspan="9"><pre>This main goal of this course is to train students with basic knowledge on digital logic design. After taking this course, students are expected to be able to design simple digital systems such as adders, multiplexers, and stop watches. The topics covered include (1) basic logic gates, (2) combinational logic design, (3) sequential logic design, (4) logic optimization, and (5) simple computer system design. </pre></td>
